- AUC stands for Area Under the Curve, a common metric for evaluating the performance of binary classification models;
- AUC values range from 0 to 1, with higher values indicating better performance;
- A threshold of 0.7 is often considered a good starting point for models to be considered effective.

sql:
SELECT percent_rank
FROM (
  SELECT PERCENT_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY size) AS percent_rank
  FROM datasets
)
LIMIT 1;

